    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">This is an all common deck ,that is, for an all common, quite effective, when taking on a bigger deck.<br />
<br />
The Free Peoples Side: <br />
Basic, get out Gandalf, and Boromir, and Aragorn.<br />
There are alot of Equips, so we have gandalf&#39;s wisdom.  Also, Not only is there TMAYOD, there is one of my favorite Siege of Gondor cards, Not the First Halfling.  This allows for your guys to Power up themselves, and Gandalf to power down minions as you do it.  All in all, I like this.<br />
Have Patience is a given, as you&#39;ll be exerting ALOT.<br />
<br />
The Shadow:<br />
Obviously, Burden, Burden, Burden.<br />
Whip out Easterlings, add burdens.<br />
Play Captured by the Ring to keep getting Gollum, and adding a Threat, then discarding him when its over, with Heavy Burden, to get rid of that threat and add a burden.  If ou are facing Ring Bound Rangers, Men of Rhun, and Old Villain help.<br />
